# Tagaddod Design System - NPM Registry Configuration
#
# This file configures where npm should fetch @tagaddod-design packages from.
#
# Copy this file to .npmrc and uncomment the configuration you need:
#   cp .npmrc.example .npmrc

# =============================================================================
# LOCAL TESTING WITH VERDACCIO (Development Mode)
# =============================================================================
# Use this when testing local package changes before publishing to npm
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. Start Verdaccio: yarn registry:start (in monorepo root)
#   2. Publish packages: yarn publish:local (in monorepo root)
#   3. Uncomment line below:

# @tagaddod-design:registry=http://localhost:4873

# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION (NPM Registry)
# =============================================================================
# Use this when using published packages from npm (default)
# This is the default behavior, no configuration needed.
#
# Uncomment line below to explicitly use npm registry:

# @tagaddod-design:registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# - Only one registry can be active at a time
# - .npmrc is git-ignored to prevent accidentally committing local config
# - Always add .npmrc to .gitignore
# - Verdaccio registry only works when Verdaccio server is running
# - npm registry requires packages to be published on npmjs.com
